    "description": "Kuribayashi Steamship Co., Ltd. engages in the marine transportation business in Japan and internationally. The company operates through four segments: Shipping Business, Hotel Business, Real Estate Business, and Other Businesses. It transports paper products, cast and forged steel products, starch, as well as handles plants, feed, ammonium sulfur, wastepaper, etc. The company also provides land and sea integrated transportation services, including loading and unloading of cargos, and collection and delivery of cargos; tugboats and barges that transport oil refinery pressure vessels for refineries and blades for wind farms; and wholesale of fruits and vegetables. In addition, it is involved in the ferry, hotel, and ship operation businesses. Further, the company leases real estate properties, such as stores. Kuribayashi Steamship Co., Ltd. was founded in 1894 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan."
